comment:
* Auxiliary application resolution response. *

* Used when resolution occurs, but, the target is not actually on the device. * This happens resolving instant apps that haven't been installed yet or if * the application consists of multiple feature splits and the needed split * hasn't been installed. * @hide

variables.name: installFailureActivity
variables.comment: The activity to launch if there's an installation failure.

variables.name: needsPhaseTwo
variables.comment: Whether or not instant resolution needs the second phase

variables.name: token
variables.comment: Opaque token to track the instant application resolution

variables.name: failureIntent
variables.comment: An intent to start upon failure to install

variables.name: filters
variables.comment: The matching filters for this resolve info.
